title: Add duration variables to panel data — add_duration
code: add_duration(   data,   y,   unitID,   tID,   freq = "month",   sort = FALSE,   ongoing = TRUE,   slice.last = FALSE )

title: Add duration variables to panel data — add_duration
text: data Data frame representing panel data. y binary indicator incidence event, e.g. coup. unitID Name variable data frame identifying cross-sectional units, e.g. "country". tID Name variable data frame identifying time unit, preferably class Date. E.g. "year". freq Frequency units measured tID. Currently yearly, monthly, daily data supported, .e. "year", "month", "day". sort Sort data unit time? Default FALSE, .e. return data original order. ongoing TRUE, successive 1's considered ongoing events treated NA first 1. FALSE, successive 1's treated failures. slice.last Set TRUE create slice last time period; used forecast.spdur. compatibility CRISP ICEWS projects.

title: Add duration variables to panel data — add_duration
text: Returns original data frame 8 duration-specific additional variables: failure Binary indicator event. ongoing Binary indicator ongoing events, counting initial failure time. end.spell Binary indicator last observation spell, either due censoring failure. cured Binary indicator spells coded cured, immune failure. Equal 1 - atrisk. atrisk Binary indicator spells coded risk failure. Equal 1 - cured. censor Binary indicator right-censored spells. duration t, counter long spell survived without failure. t.0 Starting time period observed t, default equals duration - 1.

title: Add duration variables to panel data — add_duration
text: function processes panel data frame creating failure variable y corresponding duration counter, well risk/immunity indicators. Supported time resolutions year, month, day, input data (dis-)aggregated one levels. returned data frame number rows original. y indicator incidence event, rather onset indicator, ongoing spells failure beyond initial event coded NA (e.g. 000111 becomes spell 0001 NA NA). preserve compatibility base dataset. Note order rows may different though. missing values ("NA") key variables y, unitID, tID; stop function. Furthermore, series start event, e.g. (100), treated experiencing failure first time period. events fact ongoing, e.g. last year war started start time dataset, dropped manually using buildDuration(). t.0 starting time period observation tID. default set duration - 1 currently serves placeholder allow future expansion varying observation times.

title: Add duration variables to panel data — add_duration
code: # Yearly data data <- data.frame(y=c(0,0,0,1,0),                     unitID=c(1,1,1,1,1),                     tID=c(2000, 2001, 2002, 2003, 2004)) dur.data <- add_duration(data, "y", "unitID", "tID", freq="year") #> Warning: Converting to 'Date' class with yyyy-06-30 dur.data #>   y unitID  tID failure ongoing end.spell cured atrisk censor duration t.0 #> 2 0      1 2000       0       0         0     0      1      0        1   0 #> 3 0      1 2001       0       0         0     0      1      0        2   1 #> 4 0      1 2002       0       0         0     0      1      0        3   2 #> 5 1      1 2003       1       0         1     0      1      0        4   3 #> 1 0      1 2004       0       0         1     1      0      1        1   0

title: Predict methods for spdur Objects — predict.spdur
text: Calculates various types probabilities, “conditional” used reference conditioning observed survival time spell time \(t\), addition conditioning variables included model (always done). Valid values type option include: “conditional risk”: \(Pr(Cure=0|Z\gamma, T>t)\) “conditional cure”: \(Pr(Cure=1|Z\gamma, T>t)\) “hazard”: \(Pr(T=t|T>t, C=0, X\beta) * Pr(Cure=0|Z\gamma)\) “failure”: \(Pr(T=t|T>t-1, C=0, X\beta) * Pr(Cure=0|Z\gamma)\) “unconditional risk”: \(Pr(Cure=0|Z\gamma)\) “unconditional cure”: \(Pr(Cure=1|Z\gamma)\) “conditional hazard” “response”: \(Pr(T=t|T>t, C=0, X\beta) * Pr(Cure=0|Z\gamma, T>t)\) “conditional failure”: \(Pr(T=t|T>t-1, C=0, X\beta) * Pr(Cure=0|Z\gamma, T>t)\) vector \(Z\gamma\) indicates cure/risk equation covariate vector, \(X\beta\) indicates duration equation covariate vector.

title: Split-population duration (cure) regression — spdur
text: duration formula form Y ~ X1 + X2 ..., Y duration failure censoring. atrisk formula form C ~ Z1 + Z2 ..., C binary indicator risk (1 - cure). data data frame containing variables formula formula2. last string identifying vector data indicates spell ends due failure right-censoring. t.0 starting point time-varying covariate intervals, default duration-1 using add_duration. fail Name variable indicating spell ended failure. distr type distribution use hazard rate. Valid options “weibull” “loglog”; defaults “weibull”. max.iter Maximum number iterations use likelihood maximization. na.action function indicates happen data contain NAs. default set na.action setting options, na.fail unset. silent Suppress optimization output, FALSE default. ... Optional arguments, see details.

title: Split-population duration (cure) regression — spdur
text: Returns object class spdur, attributes: coefficients named vector coefficient point estimates. vcv Estimated covariance matrix. se Standard error estimates. zstat Z-statistic values. pval P-values. mf.dur Model frame duration equation. mf.risk Model frame risk equation. Y Matrix duration variables: risk, duration, end spell, t.0. na.action action taken missing values data. call original, unevaluated spdur call. distr Distribution used hazard rate.

title: Split-population duration (cure) regression — spdur
text: See summary.spdur, predict.spdur , plot.spdur post-estimation options. Optional arguments: base.inits Initial values base duration model estimated get initial values full split-population model. needs vector starting values constant, coefficients duration equation, additional value shape parameter density used, e.g. Weibull. default 0 coefficients 0 1 Weibull LogLog shape parameters respectively.

title: Split-population duration (cure) regression — spdur
code: # Prepare data data(coups) dur.coups <- add_duration(coups, "succ.coup", unitID="gwcode", tID="year",                            freq="year")  # Estimate model model.coups <- spdur(duration ~ polity2, atrisk ~ polity2, data=dur.coups) #> Fitting base weibull... #> Fitting split weibull... #> initial  value 350.011512  #> iter  10 value 323.772940 #> iter  20 value 319.813601 #> final  value 319.809378  #> converged model.coups <- spdur(duration ~ polity2, atrisk ~ polity2, data=dur.coups,                      distr="loglog") #> Fitting base loglog... #> Fitting split loglog... #> initial  value 347.703995  #> iter  10 value 319.703145 #> iter  20 value 317.637103 #> iter  20 value 317.637101 #> iter  20 value 317.637101 #> final  value 317.637101  #> converged

title: spduration 0.17.0 (2017-10-04)
text: CRAN release: 2017-10-04 Adds proper handling various na.action options spdur predict, residuals, fitted methods. Import forecast generic function forecast package rather re-defining . Adds forecast neccessary imports. Added bug reports link DESCRIPTION github issues page (https://github.com/andybega/spduration/issues). Fixes minor errors introduction vignette data documentation. Register C++ routines avoid R-devel note.

title: spduration 0.16.0 (2017-04-11)
text: CRAN release: 2017-04-11 separationplot.spdur -> sepplot. separationplot standalone function change spdur version simple wrapper. Cleaned NAMESPACE. Moved stats imported package description removed associated explicit namespace generic imports. Added package vignette. Added file init.c calls R_registerRoutines() R_useDynamicSymbols(); also use .registration=TRUE useDynLib NAMESPACE. R-devel (R 3.4.0 future) R CMD check issues NOTE registration routines, avoid note. Updated DESCRIPTION added references.

title: spduration 0.15.1 (2016-05-12)

title: spduration 0.15.0
text: CRAN release: 2016-03-01 Added accessor methods terms, model.matrix, coef, vcov. Added fitted residuals methods. Fixes issue #17, led errors summary.spdur called model factor variables without intercept terms. Fixes issue hazard rate plot confidence intervals (plot_hazard(ci = TRUE)), CIs coud wrong coefficients sampled equation rather using full variance covariance matrix.

Replaced plot_hazard1 plot_hazard2 plot_hazard, added support loglog models, internal streamlining plotting code. Partial fix summarizing printing results models without intercept term. Removed documentation export several internal functions.
